The paper deals with the problem of identifying correlations in multivariate data under information constraints, specifically on the amount of memory and communication. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. Additionally, the paper involves trade-offs between memory/communication complexity and sample complexity, which are common themes in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions using standard distributions and studying a practical estimation problem, which could indicate a focus on Statistical Learning (cs.SI) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
